        <div class="body">
            <p>Also --provider-opts does not work.</p>

<p>The action has to have a parameter with the same name for it to work. This is very unintuitive and probably not correct.</p>

<p>The method _parseProviderOptionsPart() should not use Console GetOpt but parse the arguments left and set them as Provider Options.</p>

<p>Currently its really parsing the action arguments and setting them as additional provider arguments, although they are already set as action parameters.</p>

